Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora from neck join to moderate turn. Clay medium red-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp with amphora and thyrsus symbols.
Type series: KT2417 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 163, 17. Name Leukios.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0346)
